Okechukwu Nnodim, Abuja The Minister of Industry, Trade and Investment, Adeniyi Adebayo, has stated that he would work assiduously with his counterpart in the ministry to attract investments and boost trade in Nigeria. Adebayo said this when he resumed duties with Minister of State, Mariam Katagum, immediately after their inauguration as ministers. He disclosed that they would work hard to justify the confidence reposed in them by President Muhammadu Buhari. Adebayo said that there were enormous tasks for members of staff to carry out within the next four years of the administration. The minister said he would work with stakeholders in the ministry to achieve results, noting that he would work out plan to move the ministry forward in terms of economic growth and job creation. He assured members of staff that they would be motivated to deliver on the ministry’s policies and programmes. The Permanent Secretary in the ministry, Edet Akpan, who received the ministers, assured them of the support of members of staff to achieve the ministry’s mandate. Akpan said the ministry’s mandate was to create an environment that would stimulate industrialisation, accelerate domestic and foreign direct investment and to ensure a coordinated and integrated approach to Nigeria’s trade policy. He thereafter presented them with the handover notes containing an extract of the achievements and report of the ministry from 2015 to 2019. Copyright PUNCH.
